'''As-Suwayda Governorate''' ({{lang-ar|محافظة السويداء}}) is one of [[Syria]]'s 14 [[Governorates of Syria|governorates]]. It has an area of 5,550 km². Its capital and major city is [[As-Suwayda]].

Geographically the governorate comprises almost all of [[Jabal ad-Duruz]], the eastern part of [[Argob|Lejah]], and a part of the arid eastern steppe of [[Harrat Ash Shamah]].

==Demographics and population==
The governorate has a population of about 346,000 inhabitants (est. 2007).<ref name="cbssyr">Statistics from http://www.cbssyr.org/aindex.htm</ref>
The inhabitants of the governorate are predominantly [[Druze]] with a sizable [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Greek orthodox]] minority, there is also a small [[Muslim]] community.

Most of the inhabitants live in the western parts of the governorate, especially on the western slopes of Jabal ad-Duruz. While only nomadic [[Bedouin]] tribes live in the barren region of Harrat Ash Shamah.

